article.description: Jacob Davison had 30 points as Eastern Washington beat Portland State 89-81 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Davison lifts E. Washington past Portland St. 89-81
article.linkText: Davison lifts E. Washington past Portland St. 89-81
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. -- Jacob Davison had 30 points as Eastern Washington beat Portland State 89-81 on Saturday night. Davison shot 9 for 12 from the floor and converted 10-of-12 free throws. Mason Peatling had 22 points, 11 rebounds, five assists and three blocks for Eastern Washington (17-8, 10-4 Big Sky Conference). Casson Rouse added 11 points. Kim Aiken Jr. had 11 points and 13 rebounds. Matt Hauser had 24 points for the Vikings (12-14, 6-8). Holland Woods added 18 points and six steals. Sal Nuhu had five steals. The Eagles improve to 2-0 against the Vikings on the season. Eastern Washington defeated Portland State 71-69 on Jan. 4. Eastern Washington plays Sacramento State at home on Thursday. Portland State takes on Idaho at home on Monday. --- For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/Collegebasketball and http://twitter.com/AP-Top25 --- This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
